============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/28-1ac016c/feedback.md`. Four patterns identified:

1. **OCR digit-for-letter in first-line title** (5 failures) — extractor rejects the corrupted first line and either returns empty or falls through to a random body line. Fix: normalize digits-as-letters before scoring.

2. **Category header / metadata precedes real title** (3 failures) — line 1 is a category label (`FISH & SEAFOOD`) or pipe-delimited metadata, so the actual title on line 3 gets missed or the description line after it gets promoted instead. Fix: skip recognized non-title first-line patterns, then re-evaluate.

3. **Title absent from document start** (2 failures) — continuation pages where the recipe title never appears near the top. Extractor latches onto the first prominent string, sometimes another recipe's title. Fix: detect continuation markers and signal low confidence rather than returning a wrong answer.

4. **Mixed-case OCR corruption** (1 failure) — erratic capitalization (`KoPyTka`) makes the line fail title-pattern matching. Fix: normalize to title-case before matching.
