{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AvyjKVqcnS6mVebC3Yf41m","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the failure patterns from the digest provided and write the feedback.md file.\n\nLooking at the failures:\n\n**Pattern 1: OCR corruption - digit for letter (title on line 1)**\n- Braised Cod with White Wine: \"Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne\" → extracted nothing\n- Drożdże Sernik: \"Drożdże Sern1k\" → extracted wrong line (last/closing line)\n- Roasted Beet and Walnut Dip: \"Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p\" → extracted nothing\n- Piernik z Śliwkami: \"P1ern1k z Śliwkami\" → extracted wrong line\n\n\n- Żurek Krakowski has OCR corruption markers but the extractor fails to recognize the corrupted title as a title, either extracting nothing or pulling a random line instead.\n\n**Pattern 2: Category header before title**\n- Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce: \"FISH & SEAFOOD\" then \"Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\" → extracted a body line\n- Roasted Asparagus with Parmesan: \"VEGETABLES\" then \"Roasted Asparagus\" → similar issue where the category header throws off the title detection.\n\n**Pattern 3: Title buried mid-document**\n- Mushroom Risotto: Title appears after cooking instructions on a continuation page → extracted \"CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\" from later in the document\n- Peach Cobbler: Corrupted text from previous page obscures the title entirely → extracted an assembly instruction instead.\n\n**Pattern 4: Mixed/OCR corrupted title with special characters**\n- Kopytka z Pieczarkami Leśnymi: \"KoPyTka z P¡eczarkami Leśnymi\" → extracted a cooking step.\n\n**Pattern 5: ALL CAPS or mixed formatting for the actual title**\n- Ogórkowa Zupa: \"OGÓRKOWA ZUPA\" on line 3 after metadata → extracted nothing.\n\nLooking more closely at the failures, I'm seeing two distinct groups. The first group has OCR digit-substitution corruption in the title line itself, and the extractor can't recognize these corrupted titles at all—it returns empty or grabs body text instead. The second group involves category headers or metadata lines that push the actual title down, causing the extractor to pick the wrong line entirely.\n\nThen there are recipes where the first lines are actually mid-document fragments or cooking instructions from elsewhere in the document, so the title appears much later and gets missed. And finally, some entries have mixed case OCR corruption that's throwing off the pattern matching.\n\nLooking at this more carefully, I think the real grouping should focus on what's actually happening: some titles are corrupted with digit-for-letter substitutions right in the first line, while others have section headers or metadata lines that push the actual title down to line 3 or beyond.\n\nŻurek Krakowski is interesting because the title itself is clean on line 1, but the extractor still failed and pulled garbage from later in the file instead. That suggests the issue isn't just about OCR corruption in the title—something about how the file is structured is causing the extraction to skip over valid content entirely.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11852,"cache_read_input_tokens":10352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":11852},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"89a0634d-c744-41ac-b070-734d6b652039","uuid":"3d62aa35-aa4a-491e-88b7-7beb0c1fbb06"}
